SPRING BOOT STARTERS:
    1. Collection of dependencies grouped together.
    2. Reduces Maven configuration.


SPRING INITIALIZER:
    1. Select the dependency then you should be good to go.
    2. We can add as many dependencies as we want.
    3. There have been more than 30+ spring boot starters.

STARTER PARENT:
    1. Spring boot provides a starter parent.
    2. This provides Maven defaults.
    3. Default compiler level, and UTF-8 source encoding.
    4.
        <parent>
        	<groupId>org.springframework.boot</groupId>
        	<artifactId>spring-boot-starter-parent</artifactId>
        	<version>3.2.0</version>
        	<relativePath/> <!-- lookup parent from repository -->
        </parent>

SPRING BOOT DEV TOOLS:
    1. changing the source code forces us to re-run our application.
    2.  <dependency>
        <groupId>org.springframework.boot<groupId>
        <artifactId>spring-boot-devtools<artifactId>
        </dependency>